    • checkNaming

      private static void checkNaming() throws java.io.IOException
      Checks the naming on all reports. Compares against correctSubSiteRegex and correctAppBRegex. If it matches, pull each component and confirm that the rows in hierarchySheet corresponding to the location ID and maximo ID are the same and have all the same other components of the file name. If description varies or contains invalid characters, prompt the user with getDescription(String, String, String). If anything doesn't match, or the user skips the description prompt, add to incorrectReports and continue.
      Throws:
      java.io.IOException - if writeToInfo fails

    • handleIncorrect

      private static void handleIncorrect() throws java.io.IOException
      Processes files in incorrectReports Attempts to find year, site, location, maximo id, description, and whether the file is an App B from the name. Also attempts to pull data from the location hierarchy spreadsheet. Opens a dialog with getNameDialog(File, String, String, String, String, String, String, String, String, String, String) with all the found information to get the name, then renames the file.
      Throws:
      java.io.IOException - if writeToInfo fails
